    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Power Cylinders - Installation</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
            <title>Cylinder Sleeve Installation</title>
            <figure id="feg5346" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figh06/H06070.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Lubricate cylinder sleeve crevice seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the crevice seal with clean engine oil and install into cylinder sleeve groove
                    (without twisting).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Each cylinder sleeve has one crevice seal.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If required, ensure the proper shim(s) are installed in the crankcase counterbore
                    necessary to bring the cylinder sleeve protrusion within specifications.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the crevice seal is properly aligned in the groove.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="feg5345" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figh06/H06071.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Lubricate cylinder sleeve bore</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply clean engine oil to the lower crankcase counterbore and crevice seal bore, then
                    carefully install the cylinder sleeve.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="feg7219" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg7/EG7219.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Install cylinder sleeve</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After installation,
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_SVCPROC004.xml" xrefid="svcproc004" appearance="hottext">check cylinder
                        sleeve protrusion</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check cylinder sleeve bore dimensions and sleeve taper per
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_173.xml" xrefid="t08005" appearance="hottext">specifications</hotlnk>. If
                    the cylinder sleeve is not measuring up to specifications, check for an improperly aligned crevice
                    seal.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
